<item>
            <title>[LU-16067] quiet debugfs &quot;catastrophic mode&quot; message</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16067</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When &lt;tt&gt;debugfs&lt;/tt&gt; runs with the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;-c&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; option, it prints a scary looking message:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;catastrophic mode - not reading inode or group bitmaps
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is totally normal and expected behavior for the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;-c&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; option, which is used to significantly shorten the &lt;tt&gt;debugfs&lt;/tt&gt; command execution time by not reading metadata that isn&apos;t needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since there is often confusion about what this message means, it would be better to just avoid printing anything at all, since the use of &quot;&lt;tt&gt;-c&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is expressly requesting this behavior, and there are no messages printed out for other options.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="71594">LU-16067</key>
